name: ACTS - Drew Park (EBH)
address1: 4403 W. Martin Luther King Jr. Blvd
description: Treatment services are individualized, with different types and intensities of treatment approaches, according to the specific needs, strengths, abilities, and preferences of the person served.  Group and individual therapy sessions are provided throughout the treatment stay.  Educational groups are provided daily to address health and safety, recreation, living skills, finances, relationships, family systems, decision-making skills, nutrition, etc.  Random urine screenings are conducted.  Comprehensive case management services are provided while in treatment.  Transportation services are made available.  Room, board and supervision are provided.  Employment readiness services are provided.  All persons served will be introduced to the 12 step program and philosophy model.

name: DACCO - Community Housing Solutions Center (EBH)
description: DACCO provides temporary housing and comprehensive services to 75 residents at this location to support the goal of residents attaining permanent housing or permanent supportive housing. Basic services include food, showers, personal storage, laundry facilities and security/supervision. Services are provided on-site and/or through linkages with other community-based programs all supporting the goals of residents attaining permanent, transitional or permanent supportive housing. Individuals with a need for substance abuse treatment are linked with recovery support and other treatment services at DACCO's main campus.
service_string: Substance Use Disorder Services, Emergency Shelter

name: Family Promise of Hillsborough County - Interfaith Hospitality Network (ES)
description: Family Promise provides temporary housing, meals and case management to area homeless families.  There must be a minor child in custody.  Single, unaccompanied men or women are not eligible for the program.  A criminal background check is required, and a drug test is performed at the intake interview.  This is a 30-to-60 day program.  Families must be willing to work their case management plan with the ultimate goal of obtaining permanent housing.

unitListInfo.unitName: Family Promise of Greater Brandon, Inc - Interfaith Hospitality Network

name: Love Inc - Portico Workforce Housing
description:
Portico Workforce Housing works to transform the lives of single men struggling with homelessness in our Tampa community, in the Name of Christ, by providing an affordable housing option to single men who are actively working. Tenants are expected to contribute with chores, meet with a resource coordinator weekly, and and have a banking relationship, saving part of paycheck to go towards obtaining future traditional housing.

Call our Help Center at 813-222-LOVE (5683)

name: Mary & Martha House - Metropolitan Bridge Housing (EBH)
description: A shelter for women 18 years of age and older and their children who are homeless and/or victims of domestic violence. Offers a safe haven, classes for GED, employment readiness, computer training, parenting classes, self esteem, nutrition, job search referral, help with child care, and transportation.

name: Metropolitan Ministries - Miracle Place - Hope Hall (EBH)
description: Provides emergency shelter services for families and single women.  Provides case management, housing, employment and child care services.  Includes housing, laundry service or laundry facilities, meals or areas for meal refrigeration and preparation, clothing, transportation, furniture and household items, connection to community resources, employment services and housing access.

name: Metropolitan Ministries - Miracle Place - Uplift Emergency Shelter
description: All families in any of our emergency shelter programs are eligible for homeless housing supports as they seek resources for permanent housing.

name: Metropolitan Ministries - Offsite Emergency Bridge Housing
description: Metropolitan Ministries' of mission is to care for the homeless and those at risk of becoming homeless in our community through services that alleviate suffering, promote dignity and instill self-sufficiency as an expression of the ongoing ministry of Jesus Christ.  Metropolitan Ministries serves all who are in need and does not proselytize.  Following are the services MM provides:  Outreach and Prevention Services which include food, clothing and coordinated referrals to community resources; emergency housing and transitional housing with supportive services for families and single women and affordable housing with supportive services.  Supportive services include case management, employment services, housing services, counseling, child care, educational services (GED and K-5 partnership school) and overall access to community resources.
